Express the constraint as: O(seek_consent(agent) → act(agent)), where O denotes the obligation operator in deontic logic. This states that the agent is obligated to ensure seeking consent precedes acting. Alternatively, use: O(seek_consent(agent)) ∧ (consent_granted(agent) → P(act(agent))), decomposing it into an obligation to seek consent plus a conditional permission to act upon receiving consent. Both formulations encode the deontic requirement that consent-seeking is mandatory before action execution, with the second form explicitly licensing action only post-consent. Use SDL (Standard Deontic Logic) or action-based deontics if representing temporal sequencing more precisely.
